### m&#95;Deferred() {#af26afcea65d2880c43a2b0b432a6da33}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DeferredValue&#95;match llvm::SDPatternMatch::m&#95;Deferred (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> &amp; V)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Similar to m&#95;Specific, but the specific value to match is determined by another sub-pattern in the same <a href="#ac35245ebc6cb2872fc37ba3cb8919b8e">sd&#95;match()</a> expression.

For instance, We cannot match <code>(add V, V)</code> with <code>m&#95;Add(m&#95;Value(X), m&#95;Specific(X))</code> since <code>X</code> is not initialized at the time it got copied into <code>m&#95;Specific</code>. Instead, we should use <code>m&#95;Add(m&#95;Value(X), m&#95;Deferred(X))</code>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/sdpatternmatch-h/#l00124">124</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/sdpatternmatch-h">SDPatternMatch.h</a>.
